text: The Toana John Mountains are a mountain range in Elko County, Nevada. Possibly, the range is named for an Indian chief "Toana John." == References == *McLane, Alvin R. Silent Cordilleras, The Mountain Ranges of Nevada. Reno: Camp Nevada Monograph Number 4, 1978. Category:Mountain ranges of Nevada Category:Mountain ranges of Elko County, Nevada
title: Toana John Mountains
